        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>4 Bryanston St—</placeName>
                    <salute>My dear Romanes</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>Very many thanks— If I am able to go Huxley, I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. not be up to a talk so soon as 12<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>; but if you c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. conveniently call in the afternoon, I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. be delighted to see you.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Bryanston St—] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> <hi rend="print">‘Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.’ </hi></note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the relationship between this letter, the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13556.xml">letter to G. J. Romanes, 17 [December 1881]</ref>, and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13548.xml">letter to Francis Darwin, [18 December 1881]</ref>. </note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD stayed in London at the home of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2952.xml">Richard Buckley Litchfield</ref> and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1225.xml">Henrietta Emma Litchfield</ref> from 13 to 20 December 1881 (CD’s ‘Journal’ (Appendix II)). He visited <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2486.xml">Thomas Henry Huxley</ref> on 18 December 1881 (<ref target="./DCP-LETT-13548.xml">letter to Francis Darwin, [18 December 1881])</ref>. CD had suggested midday or afternoon for the visit in his letter to Romanes of <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13556.xml">17 [December 1881]</ref>.</note>
            
        </div>
    
